headline.main: Abroad; The Meeting at Malta and the Three-Power Conference

lead_paragraph: If, as reported, General Eisenhower is negotiating with the Badoglio Government with the approval of the Soviet, British and American Governments, the news has an important bearing on the coming three-power conference. It is clear that the arrangements made with the Italians at Malta are primarily military.
abstract: Allied Mediterranean Comm: A O McCormick on USSR and French Natl Liberation Com inclusion
